  <summary>2/11/1997--Introduced.
Amends the independent counsel statute to require the appointment of an independent counsel when the Attorney General determines that there are reasonable grounds to believe that Department of Justice employees have engaged in misconduct, criminal activity, corruption, or fraud and that further investigation is warranted.</summary>
